6:
Oh, you're finally awake. Thank
goodness.
9:
It's all right, Stella. Those robots
seem to have stopped moving as
well. We're safe.
22:
I am Stella. I am the watcher of the
Stars and observer of worlds. I am a
tool whose purpose is to purge.
33:
You mean to say that passage
between worlds is forbidden?
36:
Yes. The Overlords do not allow any
sort of interaction between worlds.
38:
That is why the existence of the
World Flippers was kept secret. And
why they can only be operated by a
select group of individuals.
42:
And any who defy the Overlords'
prohibition... are subject to a purge.
One which is carried out by
champions.
46:
The world of Pandemonium
commanded the majority of their
attention and vigilance, because of
the abyss that exists there.
51:
Indeed. It's even said that this world
was created purely in order to
contain Pandemonium.
So, this means that the royal line of
Stratos...
54:
You are the descendants of those
chosen by the Overlords. Your
primary goal was to watch over
Pandemonium, and act as stewards
of the Champion.
61:
You don't really expect me to believe
this nonsense, do you?
68:
First of all—how the hell does any of
this make sense? We're talking
about the girl who's brought
countless stragglers from different
worlds to Starview Village!
71:
You're telling me she's actually here
to STOP people from crossing
worlds? What a load of crap.
80:
I thought we told you not to
apologize!
85:
Stella. What can we do about
everything that's happening?
90:
It is no longer possible to stop this
world from merging with
Pandemonium.
94:
Every time a shift between the two
worlds occurs, the abyss grows even
wider. It will do so until it swallows up
everything in its way.
98:
If the Overlords don't purge us first,
that is.
102:
There is a person named Nova. He
seems to know more about this.
109:
You weren't thinking of sneaking
away on your own, were you?
113:
This reminds me of something I
would do—and be thoroughly
scolded for.
117:
Yeah, yeah. Let's skip the preaching
and get a move on.
126:
I am at fault. Everything is because
of me!
132:
It doesn't matter. None of that
matters to me.
143:
You're planning on going off
somewhere... and so are we. Only
makes sense that we go together!
145:
You know it too—we're stronger as a
team!
160:
I must apologize, for I cannot
accompany you on this mission.
There is simply too much work to be
done to amend the situation here.
163:
But I swear to you: One day I WILL
return to your side!
170:
The gods and their arbitrary decrees
be damned. Meeting you was my
destiny—of this I have no doubt.
173: We will fight together once more!
182:
Well, for fear of retreading the same
ground, I will be brief: I concur with
Lilith.
198:
All right, 'nuff talking! First
stop—Starview Village. I've got a
serious hankering for some grub
from our master chef here!
202:
What, now? I mean... Eh, why not. I
guess I'll whip something up! What
about you, Stella, are you hungry?
221:
The power of the curse... To think
that this is all that remains of it.
228: Oghir... Why did you leave me?
232: Why must I be alone... again?
239:
You shoulda seen it... These robots
fell from the sky, like messengers
from the heavens.
240:
I was there! I saw it all... The sky
cracked open and they started
pouring out...
248:
No, dear. Everyone's doing perfectly
well. Look, they're all unharmed.
250:
Let's go get some food in that
tummy of yours. Come along, Eric.
